  "prompt": "Is it a good thing to marry a working lady? Why and why not?",
  "response": "There are pros and cons to marrying a working woman. Here are some perspectives:\n\nPros:\n1. Financial stability and shared income\n2. Personal growth and career fulfillment\n3. Equal partnership and mutual respect\n4. Role model for children\n5. Broader life experiences and perspectives\n6. Intellectual stimulation\n7. Increased household decision-making power\n\nCons:\n1. Potential work-life balance challenges\n2. Less time for household responsibilities\n3. Possible career-related stress\n4. Childcare complications\n5. Potential conflicts in career priorities\n\nUltimately, the success of a marriage depends on:\n- Mutual understanding\n- Shared values\n- Effective communication\n- Mutual support\n- Willingness to compromise\n\nThe key is not whether a woman works, but how well partners support each other's personal and professional goals.\n\nEach couple is unique, and what works for one might not work for another. The most important factors are love, respect, and commitment.",
